Class CardServiceInsufficientMemoryException

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class CardServiceInsufficientMemoryException
extends CardServiceException
    Exception thrown when the smartcard is out of EEPROM space. This typically happens only if new data is put onto a smartcard, for example if a new applet is loaded onto a JavaCard.
